        "title": "Building a simple I/O Run Tracker App in Java. How should I store seconds and minutes?",
        "body": "<p>I'm building my first I/O app as a learning exercise in java. It will be for tracking fitness and running records. <\/p>\n\n<p>When a user is entering a new workout they will be asked to enter how long the run took them (eg 01h 02min 45sec). The only way I know how to store Date/Time in Java is with the Date class which involves miliseconds since the epoch etc...<\/p>\n\n<p>Are there any Classes available for simply creating basic \"time\" objects so I can store 20min30secs in an understandable format instead of a double (eg. 20.5mins).<\/p>\n\n<p>Cheers!<\/p>\n",
